    "name": "Lorai, Child of the Abyss",
    "subname": null,
    "lore": "The elegant Soulscryer known as Lorai has accompanied the Blacktalons for as long as they can remember. As an Idoneth of the deepest seas, she is pallid, constantly cold and somehow seems young and old at the same time. Her ageless looks conceal her long lifespan spent in service to her enclave, of which none save Hendrick is truly aware. Though she obfuscates her real motive for serving them, the Blacktalons have little reason to complain, for this talented soul-mage plays a vital role in tracking their prey across the Mortal Realms.\n\nIsharann Soulscryers are born with an innate ability to manipulate the spiritstuff of living beings, meddling with their emotions and even tugging their souls free of their bodies in extreme circumstances. Lorai, however, is a prodigy of an even darker art: the obliviating magics of the Idoneth, which allow her to shroud and erode mortal memories. Many a foe has come for the Blacktalons – assassins, hunters and agents of Chaos alike – only to stumble out of the mist in a land they have never visited, having forgotten the mission that brought them there. Though she has the gift of amnesia at her fingertips, the Blacktalons trust Lorai implicitly. Perhaps, if they knew the true reason she has worked alongside Hendrick for so long, they would not be so forgiving.",
