    "name": "Lauchon the Soulseeker",
    "subname": null,
    "lore": "When Nagash conquered Shyish, he did so by devouring all those gods who opposed him. Only a few fragments of these sundered deities endured. One such entity is the shade of Lauchon the Soulseeker, the graven boatman, who it is said knows the location of every soul in creation. A sorcerer who wishes to extricate themselves from danger may call upon Lauchon, for surely he shall find them. Yet the Soulseeker’s price is always the same: portions of the soul, devoured one sliver at a time.",
