    "name": "Suffocating Gravetide",
    "subname": null,
    "lore": "The earth of the Mortal Realms is suffused with echoes of bloodshed. A sorcerer of sufficient might can stir these energies to a form of unhallowed wakefulness, conjuring a Suffocating Gravetide. These magical constructs stink of open coffins and desiccated flesh, and their impact can crush even cavalrymen, dragging them down to face choking asphyxiation or be torn apart by the writhing spirits within. There are grim tales of Gravetides endlessly circling old battlefields or swelling with such terrible malignancy that they loom over the towering heart-trees of ancient forests.",
